<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="140" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="140">
This species can be distinguished from all other species of the genus by the following characters: in males, the median lobe of distal portion of sternum IX is enlarged with a concavity at the ventral margin, the apical margin of process of clasper is straight; in females the hilla is much narrower than width of bulga, the duct of spermatheca is connecting at cribriform area of bulga on ventral apical margin and the base of metatarsal claw do not present a sinus (see Hastriter and Mendez 2000). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mahnert" authorityYear="1982" class="Insecta" family="Tungidae" genus="Hectopsylla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hectopsylla (Hectopsylla) gracilis" order="Siphonaptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis" subGenus="Hectopsylla">Hectopsylla (Hectopsylla) gracilis</taxonomicName>
infesting 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. moreni" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" rank="species" species="moreni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">E. moreni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
constitutes a new flea-host association; this result was expected since 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H." pageId="1" pageNumber="140" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">H.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">H</emphasis>
) 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="gracilis" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been collected on 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1902" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Eligmodontia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eligmodontia hirtipes" order="Rodentia" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hirtipes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Eligmodontia hirtipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. typus" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" rank="species" species="typus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">E. typus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4103.3.3" author="Lareschi, M" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="2" pageNumber="141" pagination="239 - 258" refId="B22" refString="Lareschi, M, Sanchez, JP, Autino, AG, 2016. A review of the fleas (Insecta: Siphonaptera) from Argentina. Zootaxa 4103: 239 - 258, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4103.3.3" title="A review of the fleas (Insecta: Siphonaptera) from Argentina." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4103.3.3" volume="4103" year="2016">Lareschi et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). All localities correspond to the Monte Desert of Mountains and Isolated Valleys eco-region.
</paragraph>
